      "properties": {
        "char_end": 475,
        "char_start": 274,
        "episode_id": "79fb44f3-5be0-5fc7-9d43-2f39049f7f2d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "This episode is brought to you by Linear. Linear is the issue tracker built for speed \u2014 keyboard-first, fast search, and a clean roadmap view your team actually uses. Get started at linear.com/podcast.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 18000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 12000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:2c40947eadf74a9c",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 537,
        "char_start": 475,
        "episode_id": "79fb44f3-5be0-5fc7-9d43-2f39049f7f2d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "Why is systems thinking the part that most analyses get wrong?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:0dbf6907ce8bf5a8",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 809,
        "char_start": 557,
        "episode_id": "79fb44f3-5be0-5fc7-9d43-2f39049f7f2d",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "The short answer is Self-experimentation requires a control group of one, and that control is your own boring baseline. Teams working with WHOOP run into this constantly. The framing matters because it tells you which trade-offs you're actually making.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p09_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
